<hl>
<seg id=1> A 25-storey building in Detroit was leveled to the ground in 30 seconds. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> French News Agency, Detroit The Hudson Building with 107 years history became ruins in 30 seconds the day before yesterday. </seg>
<seg id=3> The reinforcing-bar building had 25 stores, and plastic timing explosives destroyed it. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The Hudson Building was the biggest retail market all over the world, and it's the ground symbol of Detroit. </seg>
<seg id=5> In the explosion of 1215 kg plastic timing explosive, the building became 306 million kg ruins in the end. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> At 5:45PM local time, The Hudson Building began to implode, and the thick dust developed into such a huge fog that all the audience were covered in it. </seg>
<seg id=7> A citizen said: "I can't imagine that I am blackened all over by the dust." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> When the building was falling, some of the audience cheered, but some had tears in their eyes because they couldn't see the familiar building any more. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> In the prosperous period of the 1950s, there were about 100,000 people every day going shopping in the Hudson Building. </seg>
<seg id=10> At that time, some famous film stars, e.g. Gable and Pike, visited it as well. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=11> Mayor of Detroit Orchard expressed that in order to raise US$150,000 donation, the officials wanted to give the public the chance to operate the igniter. </seg>
<seg id=12> But because the Hudson Building was the glory of the past, nobody wanted to operate the igniter to destroy the building. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=13> A man who wanted to save the building said: " It's really sad." </seg>
</p>
